						               													<description>Cogit is a cooperative game of association of ideas that takes place in 3 successive and complementary phases.&amp;#10;You will need to use your deductive sense, your imagination and your memory to find the right images and try to achieve the perfect score of 20 out of 20.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is played in 3 rounds&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the beginning, make 2 decks of 20 picture cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1st round:&amp;#10;the 1st deck is placed face-down. And the other deck is set all cards face up, all visible.&amp;#10;Reveal the first 4 cards in the 1st deck that correspond to positions 1, 2, 3 and 4. The active player secretly draws a position card (1,2, 3 or 4) and has to make the other players guess his card by showing a card from the 2nd deck by association. The other players must guess which card of the 1st deck matches.&amp;#10;If the association is correct, we reconstitute the 2 Decks separately by keeping the order of the cards. If the association is false, the cards are removed from the game. Each player plays the role of the active player in turn until there are no more cards available.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2nd round:&amp;#10;The cards are arranged in the order Deck 1 face down and Deck 2 face up just under each corresponding cards. Among the associations found, we distribute new cards to all players.&amp;#10;Each player takes turns, chooses a card from his hand and associates it under on a new 3rd line with one of the visible cards by quoting a small text telling the association of the 2 images.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3rd round:&amp;#10;All 2nd deck line cards are removed and in cooperation, the team must guess the pictures of Deck 1 cards face down. For each image found, the team scores a point. The end of this round gives the final score.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
